$ Oracle: v$SEGMENT_STATISTICS
@ v$segment_statistics

`v$segment_statistics` stores some statistical numbers about → development/databases/Oracle/architecture/database/logical-structures/segment activity.

`v$segment_statistics` deprecates `v$lock_activity` and `v$class_cache_transfer`.


gh|oracle-patterns|/Installed/dynamic-performance-views/segment_statistics/simple-test.sql||

{ statistic_name

  The possible values of `statistic_name` are found in → development/databases/Oracle/installed/dynamic-performance-views/segstat/name[`v$segstat_name`]

  gh|oracle-patterns|/Installed/dynamic-performance-views/segment_statistics/names.sql||

}

sa:

  → development/databases/Oracle/installed/dynamic-performance-views/segstat[`v$segstat`]

  → development/databases/Oracle/installed/dynamic-performance-views[Oracle Dynamic Performance Views]
